# {{ component_title }} Plugin

The **{{ component_title }}** Plugin is an extension for [Grav CMS](https://github.com/getgrav/grav). {{ component.description }}

It is scaffolded for **Grav 2.0** with the [Grav API plugin](https://github.com/getgrav/grav-plugin-api) and **Admin Next**: a REST endpoint backed by a controller, its own admin permissions, and an Admin Next sidebar item + screen.

## Requirements

- Grav 2.0+
- The `api` plugin (installed and enabled)

## Installation

Install via [GPM](https://learn.getgrav.org/cli-console/grav-cli-gpm):

    bin/gpm install {{ component_hyphenated }}

Or clone/unzip into `/user/plugins/{{ component_hyphenated }}`.

Then initialize the autoloader (required — the API controller is loaded via Composer PSR-4):

    cd user/plugins/{{ component_hyphenated }} && composer install

## What you get

| Piece | File |
|-------|------|
| REST route `GET /api/v1/{{ component_hyphenated }}/items` | `{{ component_hyphenated }}.php` (`onApiRegisterRoutes`) |
| API controller | `classes/Api/ApiController.php` |
| Admin permissions (`admin.{{ component_hyphenated }}.view` / `.manage`) | `permissions.yaml` |
| Admin Next sidebar item + screen | `{{ component_hyphenated }}.php` + `admin-next/pages/{{ component_hyphenated }}.js` |

## Trying the endpoint

The API requires an authenticated admin. Grab a token from the admin (or your API auth flow) and call:

```bash
curl -k \
  -H "X-API-Token: <your-token>" \
  https://your-site.test/api/v1/{{ component_hyphenated }}/items
```

You should get back a `{ "data": [ ... ] }` envelope.

### Permissions notes

- The generated permission `admin.{{ component_hyphenated }}.view` works as soon as the plugin is enabled.
- Super-admins bypass the check (they hold `access.api.super`, **not** the classic `admin.super`).
- Every non-super caller also needs the `api.access` permission in addition to the plugin permission.

## Usage

Edit `classes/Api/ApiController.php` to return real data, add routes in `onApiRegisterRoutes`, and build out the Admin Next screen in `admin-next/pages/{{ component_hyphenated }}.js` (a plain web component — no build step required).

